            <title>[JDK-8326101] [PPC64] Need to bailout cleanly if creation of stubs fails when code cache is out of space</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8326101</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>&lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8130309&quot; title=&quot;Need to bailout cleanly if creation of stubs fails when codecache is out of space&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8130309&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8130309&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt; has fixed most of the issues, but not all PPC64 cases. emit_exception_handler and emit_deopt_handler should also record the failure.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;quot;assert(allocates2(pc)) failed: relocation addr must be in this section&amp;quot; has been observed in JDK 11u.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
V  [libjvm.so+0xa97a70]  report_vm_error(char const*, int, char const*, char const*, ...)+0xf0&lt;br/&gt;
V  [libjvm.so+0x8cf418]  CodeSection::relocate(unsigned char*, RelocationHolder const&amp;amp;, int) [clone .part.84]+0x348&lt;br/&gt;
V  [libjvm.so+0x8cf714]  CodeSection::relocate(unsigned char*, relocInfo::relocType, int, int)+0x94&lt;br/&gt;
V  [libjvm.so+0x13a8890]  MacroAssembler::bxx64_patchable(unsigned char*, relocInfo::relocType, bool)+0x3f0&lt;br/&gt;
V  [libjvm.so+0x23decc]  HandlerImpl::emit_deopt_handler(CodeBuffer&amp;amp;)+0x9c&lt;br/&gt;
V  [libjvm.so+0x1613124]  Compile::fill_buffer(CodeBuffer*, unsigned int*)+0x2004</description>
